name: Air Elemental
text: Flying
flavor: "The East Wind, an interloper in the dominions of Westerly Weather, is an impassive-faced tyrant with a sharp poniard held behind his back for a treacherous stab."\n—Joseph Conrad, The Mirror of the Sea

name: Boomerang
text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
flavor: Early Jamuraan hunters devised a weapon that would return to its source. Tolarian Æthermancers developed a spell that skipped the weapon entirely.

name: Cancel
text: Counter target spell.

name: Cloud Sprite
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nCloud Sprite can block only creatures with flying.
flavor: The delicate sprites carry messages for Saprazzans, but they refuse to land in Mercadia City's filthy markets.

name: Counterbore
text: Counter target spell. Search its controller's graveyard, hand, and library for all cards with the same name as that spell and exile them. Then that player shuffles his or her library.

name: Deluge
text: Tap all creatures without flying.
flavor: "From the sea came all life, and to the sea it will return. The sooner the better."\n—Emperor Aboshan

name: Denizen of the Deep
text: When Denizen of the Deep enters the battlefield, return each other creature you control to its owner's hand.
flavor: According to merfolk legend, a denizen of the deep swallows the horizon at the end of each day, bringing on the cold blanket of night.

name: Essence Scatter
text: Counter target creature spell.
flavor: Some wizards compete not to summon the most interesting creatures, but to create the most interesting aftereffects when a summons goes awry.

name: Evacuation
text: Return all creatures to their owners' hands.
flavor: "Once I supply the breeze, you'll see your warriors for the smoke they truly are."\n—Alexi, zephyr mage

name: Mahamoti Djinn
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Of royal blood among the spirits of the air, the Mahamoti djinn rides on the wings of the winds. As dangerous in the gambling hall as he is in battle, he is a master of trickery and misdirection.

name: Mind Control
text: Enchant creature\nYou control enchanted creature.
flavor: "Why fight the body when you can dominate the mind that rules it?"\n—Jace Beleren

name: Mind Spring
text: Draw X cards.
flavor: Fragments of thought refract and multiply, surging in a geyser of dizzying insight.

name: Negate
text: Counter target noncreature spell.
flavor: Masters of the arcane savor a delicious irony. Their study of deep and complex arcana leads to such a simple end: the ability to say merely yes or no.

name: Phantom Warrior
text: Phantom Warrior can't be blocked.
flavor: "The construction of a defense is not accomplished by adding bricks."\n—Jace Beleren

name: Snapping Drake
text: Flying
flavor: Foul-tempered, poorly trained, and mule-stubborn, the drake is the perfect test of the master's will.

name: Thieving Magpie
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhenever Thieving Magpie deals damage to an opponent, draw a card.
flavor: Other birds collect twigs for their nests. Magpies collect jewels for theirs.

name: Unsummon
text: Return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor: Mages routinely summon creatures from the Æther. It's only fair that they occasionally throw one back.

name: Abyssal Specter
text: Flying\nWhenever Abyssal Specter deals damage to a player, that player discards a card.
flavor: To gaze under its hood is to invite death.

name: Ascendant Evincar
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nOther black creatures get +1/+1.\nNonblack creatures get -1/-1.
flavor: His soul snared by an angel's curse, Crovax twisted heroism into its purest shadow.

name: Consume Spirit
text: Spend only black mana on X.\nConsume Spirit deals X damage to target creature or player and you gain X life.

name: Crowd of Cinders
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nCrowd of Cinders's power and toughness are each equal to the number of black permanents you control.
flavor: They envy the life-giving heat so much that they tear it from those who still possess it.

name: Drudge Skeletons
text: {B}: Regenerate Drudge Skeletons. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor: "The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, never surrender, and don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."\n—Nevinyrral, Necromancer's Handbook

name: Dusk Imp
text: Flying
flavor: Imps are just intelligent enough to have an understanding of cruelty.

name: Essence Drain
text: Essence Drain deals 3 damage to target creature or player and you gain 3 life.
flavor: "The elves are right: Death inevitably leads to life. But the truly powerful don't just experience this cycle. They control it."\n—Crovax, ascendant evincar

name: Eyeblight's Ending
text: Destroy target non-Elf creature.
flavor: "Those without beauty are Lorwyn's greatest tumor. The winnowers have an unpleasant duty, but a necessary one."\n—Eidren, perfect of Lys Alana

name: Megrim
text: Whenever an opponent discards a card, Megrim deals 2 damage to that player.
flavor: "It's a vicious circle. Stress breeds pain. Pain breeds stress. It's simply beautiful, wouldn't you agree?"\n—Vradeen, vampire nocturnus

name: Mind Rot
text: Target player discards two cards.
flavor: "The beauty of mental attacks is that your victims never remember them."\n—Volrath

name: Mind Shatter
text: Target player discards X cards at random.
flavor: Dark thoughts hatch and twist within the mind, straining to take wing.

name: Moonglove Winnower
text: Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
flavor: Winnowers live to eliminate eyeblights, creatures the elves deem too ugly to exist.

name: Mortivore
text: Mortivore's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creature cards in all graveyards.\n{B}: Regenerate Mortivore.

name: Ravenous Rats
text: When Ravenous Rats enters the battlefield, target opponent discards a card.
flavor: Nothing is sacred to rats. Everything is simply another meal.

name: Sengir Vampire
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhenever a creature dealt damage by Sengir Vampire this turn dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Sengir Vampire.
flavor: Empires rise and fall, but evil is eternal.

name: Severed Legion
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor: No one in Aphetto answers a knock at the door after sundown.

name: Terror
text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Underworld Dreams
text: Whenever an opponent draws a card, Underworld Dreams deals 1 damage to him or her.
flavor: "In the drowsy dark cave of the mind, dreams build their nest with fragments dropped from day's caravan."\n—Rabindranath Tagore

name: Unholy Strength
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+1.
flavor: "Born under the moon, the second child will stumble on temptation and seek power in the dark places of the heart."\n—Codex of the Constellari

name: Act of Treason
text: Gain control of target creature until end of turn. Untap that creature. It gains haste until end of turn. (It can attack and {T} this turn.)
flavor: "Rage courses in every heart, yearning to betray its rational prison."\n—Sarkhan Vol

name: Banefire
text: Banefire deals X damage to target creature or player.\nIf X is 5 or more, Banefire can't be countered by spells or abilities and the damage can't be prevented.
flavor: For Sarkhan Vol, the dragon is the purest expression of life's savage splendor.

name: Blaze
text: Blaze deals X damage to target creature or player.

name: Bloodmark Mentor
text: Red creatures you control have first strike.
flavor: Boggarts divide the world into two categories: things you can eat, and things you have to chase down and pummel before you can eat.

name: Cinder Pyromancer
text: {T}: Cinder Pyromancer deals 1 damage to target player.\nWhenever you cast a red spell, you may untap Cinder Pyromancer.
flavor: "If the whole world burns, I'll never grow cold."

name: Earth Elemental
flavor: Earth elementals have the eternal strength of stone and the endurance of mountains. Primordially connected to the land they inhabit, they take a long-term view of things, scorning the impetuous haste of short-lived mortal creatures.

name: Enrage
text: Target creature gets +X/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The barbarians call it "touching the soul of the dragon."

name: Furnace of Rath
text: If a source would deal damage to a creature or player, it deals double that damage to that creature or player instead.
flavor: The furnace awaits the next master who would stoke the fires of apocalypse.

name: Goblin Piker
flavor: Once he'd worked out which end of the thing was sharp, he was promoted to guard duty.

name: Goblin Sky Raider
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: The goblin word for "flying" is more accurately translated as "falling slowly."

name: Hill Giant
flavor: Fortunately, hill giants have large blind spots in which a human can easily hide. Unfortunately, these blind spots are beneath the bottoms of their feet.

name: Incinerate
text: Incinerate deals 3 damage to target creature or player. A creature dealt damage this way can't be regenerated this turn.
flavor: "Yes, I think ‘toast' is an appropriate description."\n—Jaya Ballard, task mage

name: Kamahl, Pit Fighter
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\n{T}: Kamahl, Pit Fighter deals 3 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: In times when freedom seems lost, great souls arise to reclaim it.

name: Lightning Elemental
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: "A flash of the lightning, a break of the wave,\nHe passes from life to his rest in the grave."\n—William Knox, "Mortality"

name: Prodigal Pyromancer
text: {T}: Prodigal Pyromancer deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "What am I looking at? Ashes, dead man."

name: Rage Reflection
text: Creatures you control have double strike.
flavor: Vengeance is a dish best served twice.

name: Shivan Dragon
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{R}: Shivan Dragon gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The undisputed master of the mountains of Shiv.

name: Shock
text: Shock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "Once I saw a goblin shouting at a thunderstorm. He lost the argument pretty quickly."\n—Wandering mage

name: Blanchwood Armor
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 for each Forest you control.
flavor: "Before armor, there was bark. Before blades, there were thorns."\n—Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Civic Wayfinder
text: When Civic Wayfinder enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.
flavor: "These alleys are not safe. Come, I can guide you back to the market square."

name: Drove of Elves
text: Hexproof\nDrove of Elves's power and toughness are each equal to the number of green permanents you control.
flavor: "The light of beauty protects our journeys through darkness."

name: Duskdale Wurm
text: Trample (If this creature would assign enough damage to its blockers to destroy them, you may have it assign the rest of its damage to defending player or planeswalker.)

name: Elven Riders
text: Elven Riders can't be blocked except by Walls and/or creatures with flying.
flavor: "Wirewood cannot hide great size. Only with speed and skill can we survive here."

name: Elvish Champion
text: Other Elf creatures get +1/+1 and have forestwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: "For what are leaves but countless blades\nTo fight a countless foe on high."\n—Elvish hymn

name: Elvish Eulogist
text: Sacrifice Elvish Eulogist: You gain 1 life for each Elf card in your graveyard.
flavor: "No matter how adept our artistic skill, our effigies can never hope to capture the vibrant beauty of a living elf. Perhaps that is truly why we mourn."

name: Elvish Promenade
text: Put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield for each Elf you control.
flavor: The faultless and immaculate castes form the lower tiers of elvish society, with the exquisite caste above them. At the pinnacle is the perfect, a consummate blend of aristocrat and predator.

name: Elvish Visionary
text: When Elvish Visionary enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor: Before any major undertaking, a Cylian elf seeks the guidance of a visionary to learn the will of the gargantuan ancients.

name: Elvish Warrior
flavor: As graceful as a deer leaping a stream and as deadly as the wolf waiting in ambush on the other side, elvish warriors are the eyes of the forest as well as its unsheathed claws.

name: Gaea's Herald
text: Creature spells can't be countered.
flavor: "Gaea sings with the voice of nature rampant: a thousand howls, chitters, and cries, and none of them can be ignored."

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Giant Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: The giant spider's silk naturally resists gravity, almost weaving itself as it blankets the forest canopy.

name: Greenweaver Druid
text: {T}: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool.
flavor: The other tribes call them fanatics, but none deny that the Mul Daya elves have an iron-strong bond to some force greater than themselves.

name: Howl of the Night Pack
text: Put a 2/2 green Wolf creature token onto the battlefield for each Forest you control.
flavor: The murderous horrors of Raven's Run are legendary, but even that haunted place goes quiet when the night wolves howl.

name: Immaculate Magistrate
text: {T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on target creature for each Elf you control.
flavor: Elves of the immaculate class weave flora into living creatures—sometimes to endorse an elite warrior, sometimes to create a breathing work of art.

name: Imperious Perfect
text: Other Elf creatures you control get +1/+1.\n{G}, {T}: Put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: In a culture of beauty, the most beautiful are worshipped as gods.

name: Jagged-Scar Archers
text: Jagged-Scar Archers's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Elves you control.\n{T}: Jagged-Scar Archers deals damage equal to its power to target creature with flying.

name: Lys Alana Huntmaster
text: Whenever you cast an Elf spell, you may put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: From the highest tiers of Dawn's Light Palace to the deepest shade of Wren's Run, the silver notes of the horn shimmer through the air, and all who hear it feel its pull.

name: Molimo, Maro-Sorcerer
text: Trample (If this creature would assign enough damage to its blockers to destroy them, you may have it assign the rest of its damage to defending player or planeswalker.)\nMolimo, Maro-Sorcerer's power and toughness are each equal to the number of lands you control.

name: Natural Spring
text: Target player gains 8 life.
flavor: "Jewels cannot be eaten nor gold drunk. What civilization trades, nature simply provides."\n—Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Naturalize
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: If you want to destroy something lifeless, make it live.

name: Nature's Spiral
text: Return target permanent card from your graveyard to your hand. (A permanent card is an artifact, creature, enchantment, land, or planeswalker card.)
flavor: Like nature, the fern spirals back on itself, eternally seeking its own center.

name: Overrun
text: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.

name: Rampant Growth
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Nature grows solutions to its problems.

name: River Boa
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)\n{G}: Regenerate River Boa.

name: Roughshod Mentor
text: Green creatures you control have trample.

name: Runeclaw Bear
flavor: Bears aren't always as strong and as mean as you imagine. Some are even stronger and meaner.

name: Spined Wurm
flavor: Its spines act like the teeth of a saw, scoring distinctive marks in the vegetation of its territory.

name: Talara's Battalion
text: Trample\nCast Talara's Battalion only if you've cast another green spell this turn.

name: Trained Armodon
flavor: Armodons are trained to step on things. Enemy things.

name: Troll Ascetic
text: Hexproof (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities your opponents control.)\n{1}{G}: Regenerate Troll Ascetic.

name: Verdant Force
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Left to itself, nature overflows any container, overthrows any restriction, and overreaches any boundary.

name: Vigor
text: Trample\nIf damage would be dealt to a creature you control other than Vigor, prevent that damage. Put a +1/+1 counter on that creature for each 1 damage prevented this way.\nWhen Vigor is put into a graveyard from anywhere, shuffle it into its owner's library.

name: Wall of Wood
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)
flavor: Orcish lumberjacks spent the night sharpening their blades and resting for a day of labor. They awoke to find that the forest had been making its own preparations.

name: Coat of Arms
text: Each creature gets +1/+1 for each other creature on the battlefield that shares at least one creature type with it. (For example, if two Goblin Warriors and a Goblin Shaman are on the battlefield, each gets +2/+2.)
flavor: A banner for bonds of blood or belief.

name: Demon's Horn
text: Whenever a player casts a black spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: Its curve mimics the twists of life and death.

name: Dragon's Claw
text: Whenever a player casts a red spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: Though no longer attached to the hand, it still holds its adversary in its grasp.

name: Kraken's Eye
text: Whenever a player casts a blue spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: Bright as a mirror, dark as the sea.

name: Loxodon Warhammer
text: Equipped creature gets +3/+0 and has trample and lifelink.\nEquip {3}

name: The Rack
text: As The Rack enters the battlefield, choose an opponent.\nAt the beginning of the chosen player's upkeep, The Rack deals X damage to that player, where X is 3 minus the number of cards in his or her hand.

name: Wall of Spears
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\nFirst strike
flavor: "A stick is your friend. A pointed stick is your good friend. An army of pointed sticks is your best friend."\n—Onean sergeant

name: Wurm's Tooth
text: Whenever a player casts a green spell, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: A wurm knows nothing of deception. If it opens its mouth, it plans to eat you.
